<paragraph id="6BA6855303ADAA067DBFE85E2CF7A77F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Five specimens found in mosses on rock from Southwest China (YN5) (Table 
<tableCitation id="C9263B3F6C545AD0176B98BD5DF82644" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="T2" captionText="Table 2. Sampling locality information of this survey." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/14C6D5980EAD552759DE04418B45F3F2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableUuid="14C6D5980EAD552759DE04418B45F3F2">2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2861EBAC08E326C531BA166F6530A4CF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="71FC109828EEEC0CC4C7624764B7DB33" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A7440ADC607D2E847BAA47B2A4D2D72C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Body slender and transparent, integument smooth. Rostrum long and strongly bent ventrally. Rostral lamellae divided into two semi-circular lobes and wider than the anterior rim of rostrum. Head similar to hexagon, HW 89% of HL. Corona slightly narrower than collar, with papillae clearly seen in the middle of each trochus, CW 97% of HW. Trochal discs separated by a narrow, V-shaped sulcus, in which a cylindrical 
<taxonomicName id="596846199E0A5A7D47B1A3CD12C6302B" authorityName="Bryce" authorityYear="1913" class="Eurotatoria" family="Habrotrochidae" genus="Habrotrocha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="ligula" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="ligula">ligula</taxonomicName>
bends obliquely to the dorsal side (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E2D856D77934E7584EC400C34152E699" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Habrotrocha ligula loxoglotta De Koning 1947 A, B habitus, creeping, dorsal view C rostrum, lateral view D, E head, dorsal view F, G head, with ligula sloping obliquely to the dorsal side, lateral view. Scale bars: 50 μm (A, B), 10 μm (C-G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.941.50465.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/421138" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4F, G</figureCitation>
). A slight contraction near the tip which then forms a small papilla on the tip of the 
<taxonomicName id="BA7222BE277BD14AF6464270D35E7A6A" authorityName="Bryce" authorityYear="1913" class="Eurotatoria" family="Habrotrochidae" genus="Habrotrocha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="ligula" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="ligula">ligula</taxonomicName>
, attaining the level of the discs at the inner side (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="65D58CFB18446F5CAC0121423326A5E5" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Habrotrocha ligula loxoglotta De Koning 1947 A, B habitus, creeping, dorsal view C rostrum, lateral view D, E head, dorsal view F, G head, with ligula sloping obliquely to the dorsal side, lateral view. Scale bars: 50 μm (A, B), 10 μm (C-G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.941.50465.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/421138" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4D, E</figureCitation>
). Upper lip a flat bow. Neck also bent ventrally when animal creeps. The first pseudosegment of neck slightly narrower than the head at the corners of the mouth, not distinct from head and trunk. A pair of lateral cuticular bulges on the dorsal antenna pseudosegment. Antenna with two segments, its length 30-40% of the bearing pseudosegment width.
</paragraph>
<caption id="6DA63961AA94266BD2CC07D2506E84F8" doi="10.3897/zookeys.941.50465.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/421138" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 4" startId="F4">
<paragraph id="A42952188EB7DC7A23CE73BB47DC01D9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="EB8F691C0F7A1B4A5D9621E6012CF2F6" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="8AF34247FBB36B0C40C62C1905EDF1C9" authorityName="De Koning" authorityYear="1947" class="Eurotatoria" family="Habrotrochidae" genus="Habrotrocha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Habrotrocha ligula subsp. loxoglotta" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Rotifera" rank="subSpecies" species="ligula" subSpecies="loxoglotta">
<emphasis id="D7608948C41135C703DBFA78BC00A16C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Habrotrocha ligula loxoglotta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
De Koning 1947 
<emphasis id="BD8671F03C1847F115CEA57460164E85" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A, B</emphasis>
habitus, creeping, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="399E39C7FB00798CB91CA4B2E0905259" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C</emphasis>
rostrum, lateral view 
<emphasis id="CE89D2D7077781CF12EB2BBE3EA4CA31" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D, E</emphasis>
head, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="874A934F285E351EE79F25B32B47EEA0" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">F, G</emphasis>
head, with 
<taxonomicName id="DFCA8DBFC3E635A7ED3573BDEBDE6EDF" authorityName="Bryce" authorityYear="1913" class="Eurotatoria" family="Habrotrochidae" genus="Habrotrocha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="ligula" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="ligula">ligula</taxonomicName>
sloping obliquely to the dorsal side, lateral view. Scale bars: 50 
<normalizedToken id="082E0C44F081381680C24462F002907E" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(
