), 10 
<normalizedToken id="1823304C6D6588432080562DDECE2653" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="2BAE9778DDD4FB2C015A3EF34A75D628" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C-G</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="2C8CE50342878D960F5EC9D4CEBBF4D2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Trunk slender and cylindrical, TrL 59-67% of TL. Rump conical, with both pseudosegments somewhat swollen and strong arched up dorsally and roofing the foot, the posterior rim of the second pseudosegment creased, RL 8-10% of TL.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="63F815E5C17A1FA406507C9572898F83" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Foot short with three pseudosegments, FL 6-8% of TL. Bulbous spurs short and triangular shape, with distinct tips and wide interspace, base swollen. The width of interspace 114% of SL, 97% of the swollen width. Three stout unsegmented toes of the same length. Trophi small, dental formula 3/3.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
