<subSubSection id="97CDE7528365E162AEEFFE31D2DEDEE3" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="2DF5F300A8DF39CE1F989ADBDF8B4C0C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4AAA253432EEFA4AA0F1F6494C8C5C87" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="8153824D0E4186FB73A4DE1EC300FB75" authorityName="De Koning" authorityYear="1947" class="Eurotatoria" family="Habrotrochidae" genus="Habrotrocha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Habrotrocha ligula subsp. loxoglotta" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Rotifera" rank="subSpecies" species="ligula" subSpecies="loxoglotta">
<emphasis id="35DE92691211034F4E6F6A96DC13E2DF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Habrotrocha ligula loxoglotta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from Holland (De Koning 1947), later reported from beech-oak needle-litter in Germany, from dry mosses in France (
<bibRefCitation id="ABAA1C74B6B3AADA0CD1FB4294F813EE" author="Donner, J" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Jahrbuecher, Abteilung fuer Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="614 - 638" refId="B10" refString="Donner, J, 1951. Rotatorien der Humusboeden. III. Teil. Zoologische Jahrbuecher, Abteilung fuer Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere 79: 614 - 638" title="Rotatorien der Humusboeden. III. Teil." volume="79" year="1951">Donner 1951</bibRefCitation>
) and from mosses in Austria (
<bibRefCitation id="387553CF0B80F05BDD27F4AF9E5C64FE" author="Kutikova, LA" journalOrPublisher="Russian Academy of Sciences, Proceedings of the Zoological Institute, Moscow" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B30" refString="Kutikova, LA, 2005. The bdelloid rotifers of the fauna of Russia. Russian Academy of Sciences, Proceedings of the Zoological Institute, Moscow" title="The bdelloid rotifers of the fauna of Russia." year="2005">Kutikova 2005</bibRefCitation>
). In this study, it was found for the first time in China (Yunnan Province) as well as in the Oriental region.
</paragraph>
